==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: axenic
<hw>axenic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>raised under sterile
conditions; -- of experimental animals; <as>as, <ex>axenic</ex>
conditions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>pure or completely free of the presence of other
organisms; -- used of cultures of microorganisms; <as>as, an
<ex>axenic</ex> culture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> uncontaminated; germ-free.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>axerophthol</ent>⟦br⟧
